<title>COLOMBIA: Colombia in emergency measures to cut deficit.</title>
<headline>Colombia in emergency measures to cut deficit.</headline>
<dateline>BOGOTA 1997-01-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Colombian government on Monday announced emergency economic measures to cut the yawning fiscal deficit, including a drastic cut in its foreign debt programme planned for 1997.</p>
<p>Finance Minister Jose Antonio Ocampo announced a sharp reduction in the planned issuance of foreign debt bonds and unveiled a new tax on public and private sector companies, excluding exporters, that contracted fresh foreign debt.</p>
